Develop a PHP script that uses stack functions to reverse a string.

SOLUTION:
A stack works on the LIFO (Last In, First Out) principle, so we can use it to reverse a string. 
In PHP, we’ll use:
array_push() → push characters onto the stack
array_pop() → pop characters off the stack (reverses order)

CODE:
<?php
// Input string
$str = "HELLO";

// Convert string into array of characters
$chars = str_split($str);

// Initialize stack
$stack = array();

// Push all characters onto the stack
foreach ($chars as $ch) {
    array_push($stack, $ch);
}

// Pop characters from stack to build reversed string
$reversed = "";
while (!empty($stack)) {
    $reversed .= array_pop($stack);
}

// Output
echo "Original String: $str <br>";
echo "Reversed String: $reversed";
?>

OUTPUT:
Original String: HELLO <br>Reversed String: OLLEH
